==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''veto'', I forbid

===Noun===
'''veto''' (''plural:'' '''vetoes''')

#The right of a party to disapprove of and thereby stop the process of a decision, a law, etc.

====Translations====

*Danish: veto
*Dutch: veto
*Finnish: veto, [[veto-oikeus]]
*German: Veto {{n}}, [[Einspruch]] {{m}}
*French: veto {{m}}
*Polish: weto
*Spanish: veto {{m}}
*Swedish: veto

===Transitive verb===
'''to veto''' (vetoes, vetoing, vetoed)

#To use a veto against.

